  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Justice for Pacific &amp; Caribbean Women &amp; Girls</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">When women and children in Pacific Island and Caribbean region access the formal court system in gender-based violence cases, they face numerous barriers that block their pathway to justice. ICAAD&apos;s evidence (through review of 1000s of cases) shows the driving force behind this problem is gender discrimination, which includes: stereotypes, rape myths, and specific customary practices. By engaging civil society and the judiciary we use the insights from data to inform our interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
